<c.cue-0>Smishing: Smishin is a type of cyber attack that uses text messages, </c>

cue-1
00:00:04.239 --> 00:00:08.140 align:undefined
<c.cue-1>SMS or messaging apps to trick people into giving out sensitive information or </c>

cue-2
00:00:08.149 --> 00:00:10.279 align:undefined
<c.cue-2>downloading malware onto their device. </c>

cue-3
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:14.569 align:undefined
<c.cue-3>The term smishing is a combination of SMS and phishing.</c>

cue-4
00:00:15.279 --> 00:00:19.040 align:undefined
<c.cue-4>Attackers favor using SMS over email for phishing due to the high </c>

cue-5
00:00:19.049 --> 00:00:22.909 align:undefined
<c.cue-5>response rates of text messages, the cost effectiveness of bulk messaging </c>

cue-6
00:00:22.920 --> 00:00:26.780 align:undefined
<c.cue-6>through affordable SMS packages and users difficulty in differentiating </c>

cue-7
00:00:26.790 --> 00:00:30.790 align:undefined
<c.cue-7>between genuine and phishing URLS within SMS links. </c>